    <h2>2. DEFINITIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>2.1</strong> In these Terms, unless the context otherwise requires, the following definitions apply:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>"EPM" or "Equity Preservation Mortgage"</strong> means the non-traditional mortgage product offered through the Platform, whereby loan proceeds secured against residential property are invested in a managed portfolio to generate monthly income for the Borrower while preserving property equity;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>"Platform"</strong> means the FutureProof Financial website, web application, mobile application, and all associated digital interfaces and services accessible at www.futureprooffinancial.co;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>"Borrower"</strong> means a natural person who has applied for, been approved for, or entered into an EPM contract through the Platform;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>"Investment Account"</strong> means the segregated investment account established in the Borrower's name, into which EPM loan proceeds are deposited and managed in accordance with the investment strategy;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>"Holiday Period"</strong> means a temporary period during which monthly income payments to the Borrower are suspended due to adverse investment performance, with accrued income deferred until portfolio recovery;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>"NNEG" or "No Negative Equity Guarantee"</strong> means the contractual guarantee and associated insurance protection ensuring that the Borrower (or their estate) will never owe more than the market value of the secured property at the time of loan settlement;</li>
      <li>(g) <strong>"Hedging Collar"</strong> means the portfolio protection mechanism consisting of protective put options and covered call options applied to the equity component of the Investment Account to limit downside exposure;</li>
      <li>(h) <strong>"Loan-to-Value Ratio" or "LTV"</strong> means the ratio of the EPM loan amount to the independently appraised value of the secured property, expressed as a percentage;</li>
      <li>(i) <strong>"Monthly Income"</strong> means the regular payments made to the Borrower from Investment Account returns, calculated at approximately 1.5% per annum of the property value, paid monthly in arrears;</li>
      <li>(j) <strong>"Property"</strong> means the residential real property owned by the Borrower that serves as security for the EPM;</li>
      <li>(k) <strong>"Profit Share"</strong> means the periodic distribution of surplus investment returns to the Borrower, calculated and paid every five (5) years during the loan term;</li>
      <li>(l) <strong>"Lender"</strong> means the licensed mortgage lender that provides the EPM loan funds through the Platform;</li>
      <li>(m) <strong>"Investment Manager"</strong> means the SEC-registered investment adviser appointed by FutureProof to manage the Investment Account portfolio;</li>
      <li>(n) <strong>"Valuation"</strong> means the independent appraisal of the Property conducted by a licensed appraiser in accordance with Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice (USPAP).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. SERVICE DESCRIPTION</h2>
    <p><strong>3.1</strong> FutureProof operates a technology platform that facilitates the origination, management, and servicing of Equity Preservation Mortgages. The Platform connects Borrowers with licensed Lenders, Investment Managers, and ancillary service providers.</p>
    <p><strong>3.2</strong> The EPM product works as follows:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) The Borrower applies for a mortgage secured against their residential property;</li>
      <li>(b) Upon approval, loan proceeds are advanced by the Lender and deposited into a segregated Investment Account;</li>
      <li>(c) The Investment Account is managed by the Investment Manager in accordance with a diversified investment strategy comprising approximately 70% equity index-linked ETFs (primarily S&amp;P 500 tracking) and approximately 30% fixed income securities;</li>
      <li>(d) A Hedging Collar is applied to the equity component to provide downside protection;</li>
      <li>(e) Investment returns are used to service the mortgage interest payments and generate Monthly Income for the Borrower;</li>
      <li>(f) The Borrower receives Monthly Income of approximately 1.5% per annum of the property value;</li>
      <li>(g) At the end of the loan term, or upon sale of the Property, the mortgage is repaid from the Investment Account and any surplus is returned to the Borrower;</li>
      <li>(h) The NNEG ensures the Borrower never owes more than the property value.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>3.3</strong> FutureProof acts as a platform operator and mortgage servicer. FutureProof is not the Lender and does not provide investment advice. All lending decisions are made by the Lender, and all investment management decisions are made by the Investment Manager.</p>
    <p><strong>3.4</strong> The Platform also provides ancillary services including financial calculators, educational content, document management, and customer support.</p>

    <h2>4. ELIGIBILITY</h2>
    <p><strong>4.1</strong> To use the Platform and apply for an EPM, you must satisfy all of the following criteria:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Be aged fifty-five (55) years or older at the time of application;</li>
      <li>(b) Be a United States citizen or lawful permanent resident;</li>
      <li>(c) Own residential real property located in the United States with an independently appraised value of not less than five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000);</li>
      <li>(d) The Property must be your primary residence;</li>
      <li>(e) Successfully pass credit assessment, identity verification, and anti-money laundering checks as required by the <%= details[:aml_act] %>;</li>
      <li>(f) Have legal capacity to enter into a mortgage contract and to grant a security interest in the Property;</li>
      <li>(g) Not be an undischarged bankrupt, subject to insolvency proceedings, or subject to any court order restricting financial transactions;</li>
      <li>(h) Not have any existing liens, judgments, or encumbrances on the Property that would prevent the Lender from obtaining a first-priority mortgage lien, unless such encumbrances can be satisfied from loan proceeds at closing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>4.2</strong> Meeting the eligibility criteria does not guarantee approval. All applications are subject to underwriting by the Lender, property valuation, and credit assessment.</p>
    <p><strong>4.3</strong> You represent and warrant that all information provided in connection with your application is true, accurate, complete, and not misleading. Providing false or misleading information may constitute federal mortgage fraud under 18 U.S.C. Section 1014.</p>

