    <h2>6. EPM PRODUCT TERMS</h2>
    <p><strong>6.1 Loan-to-Value Ratio:</strong> The maximum LTV for an EPM is eighty percent (80%) of the independently appraised value of the Property. The actual LTV approved will depend on the Borrower's age, property type, location, and credit profile.</p>
    <p><strong>6.2 Loan Terms:</strong> EPM loans are available for terms of ten (10), fifteen (15), twenty (20), twenty-five (25), or thirty (30) years. The appropriate term will be determined based on the Borrower's age, financial circumstances, and preferences.</p>
    <p><strong>6.3 Investment Strategy:</strong> Loan proceeds deposited in the Investment Account are invested in accordance with the following strategy:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Approximately seventy percent (70%) in equity index-linked exchange-traded funds (ETFs), primarily tracking the S&amp;P 500 Index;</li>
      <li>(b) Approximately thirty percent (30%) in fixed income securities, including government bonds and investment-grade corporate bonds;</li>
      <li>(c) A Hedging Collar is applied to the equity component, consisting of protective put options to limit downside risk and covered call options to generate additional income;</li>
      <li>(d) The Investment Manager may make tactical adjustments within approved parameters based on market conditions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>6.4 Monthly Income Payments:</strong> The Borrower receives Monthly Income calculated at approximately 1.5% per annum of the property value, paid monthly in arrears. The exact amount is determined at origination and may be adjusted in accordance with the EPM contract terms. Monthly Income is sourced from investment returns and is not a drawdown of equity.</p>
    <p><strong>6.5 Profit Share:</strong> Every five (5) years during the loan term, surplus investment returns (returns exceeding those required for interest payments, Monthly Income, and fees) are calculated and distributed to the Borrower as a Profit Share payment.</p>
    <p><strong>6.6 Interest Rate:</strong> The interest rate applicable to the EPM will be disclosed in the Loan Estimate and Closing Disclosure in accordance with TILA requirements, expressed as an <%= details[:interest_disclosure] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>6.7 Equity Preservation:</strong> The EPM is designed to preserve one hundred percent (100%) of the Borrower's property equity throughout the loan term. Interest and fees are paid from investment returns, not from the Borrower's equity.</p>

    <h2>7. FEES AND CHARGES</h2>
    <p><strong>7.1</strong> The following fees and charges apply to EPM products. All fees will be disclosed in full in the Loan Estimate provided before you commit to the application, in compliance with TILA and RESPA:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Application Fee:</strong> A non-refundable fee payable upon submission of a formal EPM application, as disclosed in the Loan Estimate;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Valuation Fee:</strong> The cost of the independent property appraisal conducted by a USPAP-compliant appraiser, payable by the Borrower;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI):</strong> A one-time premium of 1.6% of the loan amount, payable at closing and deducted from loan proceeds;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Platform Fee:</strong> An ongoing fee of 0.25% per annum of the Investment Account balance, deducted monthly from investment returns;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>Hedging Fee:</strong> An ongoing fee of 0.25% per annum of the equity portfolio value, covering the cost of maintaining the Hedging Collar, deducted monthly from investment returns;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>Legal and Settlement Fees:</strong> Third-party costs associated with loan closing, title insurance, recording fees, and other settlement services, as itemized in the Closing Disclosure;</li>
      <li>(g) <strong>Early Termination Fee:</strong> If applicable, as disclosed in the EPM contract. Any prepayment penalties will comply with applicable federal and state law.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>7.2</strong> All fees are disclosed in the Loan Estimate and Closing Disclosure before you commit to the application. You have the right to shop for third-party settlement services as permitted under RESPA.</p>
    <p><strong>7.3</strong> FutureProof does not charge hidden fees. If any fee changes during the application process, you will be notified in writing and provided with an updated Closing Disclosure at least three (3) business days before closing.</p>

    <h2>8. INVESTMENT RISKS AND DISCLAIMERS</h2>
    <p><strong>8.1</strong> You acknowledge and agree that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Market Risk:</strong> The Investment Account is subject to market fluctuations. The value of investments may go down as well as up. Past performance is not indicative of future results;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Income Variability:</strong> While Monthly Income is targeted at approximately 1.5% per annum of property value, actual payments may be reduced or suspended during Holiday Periods if investment returns are insufficient;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>No Guaranteed Returns:</strong> FutureProof, the Lender, and the Investment Manager do not guarantee any specific level of investment return, income amount, or profit share;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Hedging Limitations:</strong> The Hedging Collar reduces but does not eliminate investment risk. In extreme market conditions, losses may exceed the protection provided by the collar;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>Concentration Risk:</strong> The equity component is primarily invested in S&amp;P 500 tracking ETFs, which means performance is concentrated in the U.S. large-cap equity market;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>Interest Rate Risk:</strong> Changes in interest rates may affect the fixed income component of the portfolio and the overall investment return;</li>
      <li>(g) <strong>Counterparty Risk:</strong> The EPM involves multiple counterparties including the Lender, Investment Manager, and insurers. The failure of any counterparty could affect the operation of the EPM.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>8.2</strong> All projections, estimates, and illustrations provided through the Platform are based on historical data and financial modelling. They are provided for informational purposes only and should not be relied upon as predictions of future performance.</p>
    <p><strong>8.3</strong> You should obtain independent financial, legal, and tax advice before entering into an EPM. FutureProof does not provide financial, investment, legal, or tax advice.</p>

    <h2>9. HOLIDAY MECHANISM</h2>
    <p><strong>9.1</strong> The Holiday Mechanism is a protective feature of the EPM designed to preserve the long-term sustainability of the investment portfolio during periods of adverse market performance.</p>
    <p><strong>9.2</strong> A Holiday Period is triggered when the Investment Account balance falls below the minimum threshold required to sustain Monthly Income payments while maintaining the integrity of the overall investment strategy. Specifically:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) If investment returns in any period are insufficient to cover both the mortgage interest payment and the Monthly Income payment, the Monthly Income payment will be suspended;</li>
      <li>(b) Mortgage interest payments continue to be serviced from the Investment Account during a Holiday Period;</li>
      <li>(c) Suspended Monthly Income accrues and is paid to the Borrower when the portfolio recovers to a level sufficient to resume payments;</li>
      <li>(d) The Holiday Period ends automatically when the Investment Account recovers to the required threshold.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>9.3</strong> During a Holiday Period, you will be notified in writing, and the Platform will provide regular updates on portfolio performance and the expected timeline for resumption of payments.</p>
    <p><strong>9.4</strong> The Holiday Mechanism is designed to protect the Investment Account from forced selling of assets during market downturns, thereby preserving long-term portfolio value and your equity.</p>

    <h2>10. INSURANCE AND PROTECTION</h2>
    <p><strong>10.1 No Negative Equity Guarantee (NNEG):</strong> Every EPM includes NNEG protection, which guarantees that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) The Borrower (or their estate) will never owe more than the market value of the Property at the time of loan settlement;</li>
      <li>(b) If the outstanding loan balance exceeds the property value at settlement (due to sustained market decline), the NNEG insurance absorbs the shortfall;</li>
      <li>(c) No deficiency judgment can be pursued against the Borrower or their estate for any amount exceeding the property value;</li>
      <li>(d) NNEG protection remains in force for the entire duration of the EPM, regardless of market conditions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>10.2 Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI):</strong> LMI is required on all EPM loans and provides additional protection to the Lender. The LMI premium of 1.6% of the loan amount is a one-time charge deducted from loan proceeds at closing.</p>
    <p><strong>10.3 Hedging Collar Protection:</strong> The Hedging Collar applied to the equity portfolio provides structural protection against significant market downturns by limiting the maximum loss on the equity component to a predefined range.</p>

    <h2>11. PROPERTY OBLIGATIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>11.1</strong> As a condition of the EPM, you agree to maintain the following obligations with respect to the Property throughout the loan term:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Insurance:</strong> Maintain comprehensive homeowners insurance on the Property at all times, with coverage at least equal to the replacement cost of the dwelling, naming the Lender as loss payee. Proof of insurance must be provided annually;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Property Taxes:</strong> Pay all real property taxes, assessments, and government charges when due. Failure to pay property taxes constitutes an event of default;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Maintenance:</strong> Maintain the Property in good condition and repair, and not permit waste, deterioration, or destruction. You must not make material alterations to the Property without prior written consent of the Lender;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Primary Residence:</strong> Occupy the Property as your primary residence throughout the loan term. You must notify FutureProof immediately if the Property ceases to be your primary residence, as this may constitute an event of default;</li>
      <li>(e) <strong>No Additional Liens:</strong> Not create, permit, or suffer any additional liens, mortgages, or encumbrances on the Property without the prior written consent of the Lender;</li>
      <li>(f) <strong>Compliance with Laws:</strong> Comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, ordinances, regulations, and restrictive covenants affecting the Property;</li>
      <li>(g) <strong>Flood Insurance:</strong> If the Property is located in a Special Flood Hazard Area as determined by the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), maintain flood insurance as required by the National Flood Insurance Act;</li>
      <li>(h) <strong>Condominium/HOA Compliance:</strong> If applicable, comply with all condominium or homeowners association rules and pay all assessments when due.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>11.2</strong> Failure to comply with any of the obligations set forth in Section 11.1 may constitute an event of default under the EPM contract, entitling the Lender to exercise its remedies, including acceleration of the loan.</p>

